# Git Commit Message Convention

This project follows the **Conventional Commits** specification to standardize commit messages. All developers are required to follow this structure to ensure consistent commit history, making it easier to collaborate and maintain the codebase.

# Commit Message Format

<type>(<scope>): <subject>

# Commit Message Example

feat(login): add login authentication with JWT
fix(api): correct bug in query handling
docs: update README with installation instructions
style: format code according to ESLint rules
refactor(database): optimize query for faster execution

